items.Video_Title: Alteration HACK for Beginner Sewers! (How To Alter Your Pants) DIY with Orly Shani
items.Video_Description:
Join me, Orly Shani, as I show you my favorite hack to alter my pants!!

SHOP MY NEW MERCH! - https://store.thediydesigner.com/
Promo code - freeover50 (free shipping over $50)
SHOP HANDMADE : https://www.orlyshani.com

Check out my latest videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL2Ml7kFlBsR0zcOuPhefnLDgTjZRM1RpP
Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCSWqS4gVZEUOIS345CKRmPA/?sub_confirmation=1 

In this video I show you a super simple  hack for altering pants that are either too big on you or not the right shape. It started with a pair of Army Surplus Cargo Pants which fit me great on top, but were a little too baggy on the bottom. 
I know baggy pants are in! But to me, these werent baggy ENOUGH... they were sort of in no man's land. So I decided to taper them! I did the full DIY on IG stories which obviously expired. But I'm doing a ton more LIVE DIY's on Stories so be sure to follow me there. 
INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/orlyshani

I decided re-created this in order to show you in more detail.
1) Tan Cargo Pants - I taper the leg, take in the waist and the seat.
2) Blue Camos - I only taper the leg. 

Hopefully this hack will help you save some money on alterations. Is it the most proper alteration? Nope, but I never claimed to be a seamstress lol.

Have fun!

If you try my DIYs, make sure to tag me on my socials!
INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/orlyshani
TWITTER: https://twitter.com/orlyshani

items.Video_Description:
This video is an in depth review of the Aritzia Modern Cargo Pant, Ascendant Pant, Effortless Pant and Melina Pant. 

Though I'm looking out my window typing this and seeing snow falling spring is truly right around the corner. With temperatures hovering in the single digits it's not quite time to break out the floral dresses. But that doesn't mean we can't brighten our wardrobes and still be functional. Today I want to share 4 of my personal favourite (3 new and 1 old) Aritzia pants that you can shop in store or online now. 

I've been searching for my personal style for years but this is the first time I can confidently say I know exactly where I want my style to go! Exciting times. Not only is this allowing me to pair down my wardrobe but also to shop more intentionally and smarter when it comes to introducing each and every piece. I see this less as a huge haul and more as an intentional shopping practice and I hope you do too! 

Extra shout out to Nancy at the Mapleview Mall Aritzia location for introducing me to the Ascendent pant and helping me try on essentially every colour pant in store! Finding a stylist you trust and can relate to can truly change the game when you are in the change room!
